summary: Team Recess Vinyasa Yoga Class at Yess Yoga
description: Vinyasa yoga class organized by Team Recess to support longtime sponsor Yess Yoga. When: Tuesday, March 3rd from 6-7pm Location: Yess Yoga Registration: Required through Yess Yoga website before the class. Drop-in rate is $20/class. New student rates and multi-class packages available. About Vinyasa: Vinyasa is defined as "to move in a special way" - flowing movement sequences that vary each class. Focus on safe alignment and encouraging personal yoga practice exploration. Yoga mats available for use at the studio. Link: https://www.instagram.com/p/DVMJ5fLjImu/
location: Yess Yoga, 105 E 26th St, Minneapolis, MN 55404, USA

extra_metadata.post_content:
Community support is more important than ever. Please join us in supporting our longtime sponsor, Yess Yoga, by joining us for a Vinyasa yoga class on Tuesday, March 3rd from 6-7pm. Yess Yoga has the most amazing studio, instructors, and vibe and we can’t wait to introduce you if you’ve never been! Yess Yoga will have yoga mats available for use. A note on the yoga class: You’ll need to register for the class through Yess Yoga before the ride. Registration happens on their website. Yess’ drop-in rate is $20/class, and they also offer new student rates and multi-class packages. Contact Yess for more information. About Vinyasa- Vinyasa is defined as “to move in a special way”, we try to take that definition to heart each time and bring a group of students together by moving through unique sequences. A vinyasa class can be big flowing movement on each breath or slower movements to explore depth. No class is ever the same as the students in the room are never the same. Our main focus for each class are safe alignment and encouraging each student to explore their personal yoga practice.

description: Community coffee meetup at El Paraiso Supermarket to support this local Ecuadorian business. Time: 10:00 AM on the sidewalk in front of El Paraiso. Optional: 9am yoga (free) at Recovery Bike Shop beforehand. Location: El Paraiso Supermarket (29th and Central, Northeast Minneapolis) All are welcome. Bring your own coffee or buy a cup inside the market. Recovery Bike Shop will bring treats to share. Make sure to go inside and explore the supermarket and their recently reopened restaurant with Ecuadorian breakfast menu! This event is part of the "What Can I Do?" community support series. Link: https://www.instagram.com/p/DVTiS_9jrdl/

extra_metadata.post_content:
This Coffee (Outside) on Sunday at 10am comes by request from a community member that wants to see El Paraiso Supermarket get the support they need. (29th and Central). First, El Paraiso is so much more than meets the eye. Most important to me is the reopening of their restaurant including their Ecuadorian BREAKFAST menu! El Paraiso has been through a lot. The guy that runs the kitchen is still being illegally detained in Texas with no end in sight. Paraiso opened late last year and immediately went straight into the ICE invasion. And they’ve been working hard to get back to full operations. Come to Recovery Bike Shop for 9am yoga (free). Then join us at 10:00 on the sidewalk in front of El Paraiso. But make sure to go inside and explore. The no-frills storefront does not do justice to everything available inside. All are welcome. Bring your own coffee or buy a cup inside the market (or not at all). We’ bring some delicious treats to share. Can’t wait to see you! PHOTO: Miryan with El Paraiso’s full menu! We are #NortheastMinneapolis #Mpls #WhatCanIdo #EatDrinkDishMpls #Humanity_Shots

description:
Group ride (no-drop)  

Freewheel Minnetonka Monday gravel/MTB rides

When: Roll at 6:30pm, every Monday year round, weather permitting

Where: Freewheel Bike Minnetonka (10750 Cedar Bend, Minnetonka, MN 55305)  

Rides are 90 minutes leaving at 6:30 PM with food and beverages provided by the shop after the ride around 8 PM.

Link: https://www.strava.com/clubs/470025  

Summer Gravel ride and mountain bike rides

Distance: 10-15 miles

Pace: 10-15 mph (gravel group is more casual while mountain bike group is faster paced)

What to bring: Gravel bike (any bike you can ride on ill maintained roads is fine) or Mountain bike, helmet, head and tail lights for when the sun sets before 8PM. 

Both rides are offered most weeks. Gravel ride is chill pace 10-15 miles in 90 minutes, no drop, and almost any bike will do. Mountain bike rides are faster paced and ride 4-5 miles out to Theodore Wirth or Lone Lake park and back. 

Rides are canceled if weather/trails are not cooperating so check the Freewheel Strava page for updates day of.

Winter Fat Bike Rides:

Distance: 5-10ish miles on hand built singletrack, bike paths, unplowed railroad service road,  frozen lakes, and sometimes the Minnehaha creek

Pace: no drop, depends on group and conditions. 5mph is normal on fatbikes

What to bring: Fat Bike (ideally with studded tires), helmet, head and tail lights,  gear for the weather (gloves, buff, hat, boots, etc.). 

Heavy E-fat bikes not recommended since the bike will need to be lifted over rail road tracks to reach the trails.
location: Freewheel Bike Minnetonka, 10750 Cedar Bend, Minnetonka, MN 55305, USA

description:
Group ride (no-drop) Angry Catfish Wednesday social ride. Instagram. Discord. Website.

When: Wednesday Oct 1, 2025 rolling at 6:00 pm. First Wednesday of each month during cold weather months.

Start: Angry Catfish Bicycle Finish: Venn Brewing Company

Distance: ~15 miles. Pace: 12-13 mph.

Bring lights, dress for the weather. Led by: Alex & Adam

Some additional considerations as weather gets colder:
- Dress for the weather, we will ride even when the temperature gets real low. Layers, pogies, and toe warmers are your friends. Ask friends how they layer, experiment and enjoy the thrill of winter riding.
- Ride based on your comfort level - rides will be in the dark and can be icy/snowy. Studded and/or fat tires encouraged in the depths of winter. Lights required.

Led by: Alex & Adam.

See Discord link for ride updates.
location: Angry Catfish Bicycle, 2900 E 42nd St, Minneapolis, MN 55406, USA

description:
Self-supported ride TWOHUNDOFUNDO Instagram

Saturday Jul 18, 2026 4:00 AM

Start: Brackett Park End: South Minneapolis

Distance: Up to 200 miles in a loop around the cities. Choose your own adventure, self-supported ride. Bring tools, flat fixing kit, food, water, and whatever else you need to be out biking all day.


Description: “A 200 mile ride, starting and ending in South MInneapolis, born from the dream of a mixed terrain, ultra-endurance ride that was accessible to the masses. Sleep in your own bed the night before and the night after, no spending hours on traveling to the event, or spending hundreds of dollars.

The perfect training ride, with numerous pull off points to make the ride as long or as short as you need. Biking through urban areas so you don’t need to worry about being stranded, or having to pay thousands of dollars for a medevac, it’s a quick little Uber ride home.

Start at the beginning and go as long as you can, you will be surprised how far you go! Or meet up with some friends mid-route, and help them keep the party going! A true choose-your-own-adventure, unsanctioned and unsupported, the day is what you make it! Lot of places to rest, and even more places to turn off and shorten the ride, the stakes have never been lower!”
location: Brackett Park, 2728 S 39th Ave, Minneapolis, MN 55406, USA
